Hello Jing,

Using default settings with the seed http://uk.blackberry.com, these server-relative links should be in scope. It could take a long time before they are fetched.  Are you certain they are never fetched, even when you let the crawl run to completion? If so, your scope rules may be excluding them. You could try enabling logToFile on the scope bean to find the guilty scope rule.

To include in scope all subdomains of uk.blackberry.com you could add the surt +http://(com,blackberry,uk, to your SurtPrefixedDecideRule. (For the links you mention though that won&#39;t be necessary because they are on the same domain. Also, if you&#39;re using http://uk.blackberry.com as your seed, with no trailing slash, with default settings, subdomains will already be in scope.)

Noah

